The paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for the classification of dermoscopy images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also mentioned as a solution to the issue of providing quality care to patients in areas lacking access to trained dermatologists. Additionally, the paper discusses the HAM10000 dataset, which is a medical dataset, placing it under the medical informatics (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the accuracy of the model, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
